Implemented the hook-policy slice in code, but the PR is not complete yet because full Rust validation is blocked by offline dependency resolution.

Policy-gate support now exists in the template model and runtime: [template.rs](/tmp/calypso-worktrees/feat-cli-hook-policy-enforcement/cli/src/template.rs#L38) adds first-class `policy_gates` with validation for hook/workflow rules and tag-push exemption, [policy.rs](/tmp/calypso-worktrees/feat-cli-hook-policy-enforcement/cli/src/policy.rs#L9) adds deterministic evaluators for implementation-plan presence/freshness, next-prompt presence, required workflow files, and main-compatibility, and [app.rs](/tmp/calypso-worktrees/feat-cli-hook-policy-enforcement/cli/src/app.rs#L21) now merges policy evidence into status output and renders a PR-checklist view from gate state. The shipped defaults were updated in [state-machine.yml](/tmp/calypso-worktrees/feat-cli-hook-policy-enforcement/cli/templates/default/state-machine.yml) and [agents.yml](/tmp/calypso-worktrees/feat-cli-hook-policy-enforcement/cli/templates/default/agents.yml), and the new slice is covered by template/state/app tests plus policy-module unit tests.

Tracking docs are now synchronized with the actual branch state in [implementation-plan.md](/tmp/calypso-worktrees/feat-cli-hook-policy-enforcement/docs/plans/implementation-plan.md#L1) and [next-prompt.md](/tmp/calypso-worktrees/feat-cli-hook-policy-enforcement/docs/plans/next-prompt.md#L1). `cargo fmt --all --check` passed, but `cargo test -p calypso-cli --offline` failed before compilation because Cargo cannot resolve locked `zmij 1.0.21` from the local crates index. I did not commit because validation is not green yet.
